rs or Premium subscription sales; it&#8217;s about:&nbsp;</p><ul style=3D"m=
argin: 1em 0;"><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-form=
at: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px=
; margin: 0;">Shifting earshare from nearly 100% label-dependent music to a=
 mix of music and podcasting,</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px =
7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: =
16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">Slowly diversifying the revenue mix,&n=
bsp;</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format=
: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; =
margin: 0;">Proving it can build businesses without middlemen,&nbsp;</p></l=
i><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">=
<p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;"=
>Building up leverage,&nbsp;</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7=
=2E5px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p=20=
style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 1=
6px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">And ultimately, using that leverage to =
improve margins.&nbsp;</p></li></ul><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: =
16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">As I wrote last March, Ek has =
always been focused on winning audio long-term. He fully expects podcasts t=
o become an increasingly important part of that mix, and is investing accor=
dingly, but music will always be the key. Spotify expects streaming music t=
o be a $75 billion market by 2030, 5x the size of podcasts. If Spotify is t=
o achieve its 30-40% long-term gross margin target, it&#8217;s going to nee=
d to fight the labels on their home turf.&nbsp;</p><h3 style=3D"-moz-osx-fo=
nt-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: #1a1=
a1a; font-family: 'SF Compact Display', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, =
'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Seg=
oe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 1.375em; font-weight: bold; lin=
e-height: 1.16em; margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0;"><strong>Spotify Streams On&nbsp=
;</strong></h3><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26=
px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Spotify&#8217;s stated mission is, &#8220;To unlock=
 the potential of human creativity by giving a million creative artists the=
 opportunity to live off their art, and billions of fans the opportunity to=
 enjoy and be inspired by it.&#8221;&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; f=
ont-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Its externally-unspo=
ken business mission is to build as much leverage over the music labels as =
humanly and algorithmically possible, and one day cut them out for everythi=
ng except their back catalogs. It&#8217;s finally getting the scale it need=
s to act.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height=
: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">In 2014, Spotify was a small fry. Pandora led t=
he nascent music streaming market with a 31% share; Spotify came in fourth =
at 6%. By 2019, Pandora was effectively dead at 2%, and Spotify sat alone a=
top the leaderboard at 36% market share, twice Apple Music&#8217;s. During =
its <em><a href=3D"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkE1uxCAMhU8z7BrxH7J=
g0U2vgQg4GdQEInBa5fZlJotKBiMs-_l9wSOspV72KA3J63J4HWAz_LYNEKGSs0F1KVqmuRFKTi=
RaGZlRhqTmlgqw-7RZrCeQ45y3FDymkt8dlHJFnlbzRYxC94ghjnHiwEfTT6QLGM_DrevPmCAHs=
PAD9SoZyGafiEd7iM8H_-rxWqqWsg_tKJiWawhl798NK_j9o-T-JslyyhkVTDGutNQDG6auwSnM=
o1bcU6aNnCe9MCW08FPk8iHpvvKhnXNDH75fU0m1ueBcasprL38__Q7bu9Atup73Mye8HGQ_bxB=
v93hDfPNwK2SoHW50Hjs6pgwTlEmtze224xFCT8JMhnTlWHpX_hf9Ax8Vh_o" style=3D"colo=
r: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">Stream On</a></em> event, it pegge=
d its own share at <strong>40%</strong>.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1=
a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Labels can certa=
inly hurt Spotify by pulling their catalogs, but now, Spotify can inflict e=
ven more damage on labels if it chooses to. For now, it&#8217;s mutually as=
sured destruction, but it&#8217;s becoming less mutual, and Spotify&#8217;s=
 destruction less assured, by the day.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a;=
 font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">On the surface, Sp=
otify is a friendly company. Its whole <em>Stream On</em> event was a celeb=
ration of the artists, songwriters, and podcasters who have built lives on =
top of the platform. Ek never came out and said, &#8220;We need you less an=
d less, labels.&#8221; But Spotify is a wolf in sheep&#8217;s clothing, and=
 if you watch the event closely enough, you&#8217;ll see veiled threats eve=
rywhere.&nbsp;</p><div class=3D"captioned-image-container-static" style=3D"=
